description: Origin obscure. Perhaps from Middle English strupen, a variant of strepen (“to strip, rob, plunder”), from Old English *strȳpan (attested in Old English bestrȳpan (“to strip, rob, spoil, bereave”), whence English bestrip). More at strip.

verbs.description: strub (third-person singular simple present strubs, present participle strubbing, simple past and past participle strubbed)

entries.meaning: (UK, dialect, transitive, intransitive) To rob, plunder; clear out completely; to strip.
